General.Name: iShares S&P Small-Cap 600 Growth ETF
General.Description: The index measures the performance of the small-capitalization growth sector of the U.S. equity market. The fund generally will invest at least 80% of its assets in the component securities of its index and in investments that have economic characteristics that are substantially identical to the component securities of its index and may invest up to 20% of its assets in certain futures, options and swap contracts, cash and cash equivalents.
